<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: DEATH PENALTY TO BE SOUGHT IN ACTRESS' 
MURDER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Prosecutors said Thursday they will seek the death penalty for an obsessed fan 
accused of murdering actress Rebecca Schaeffer -- unless the defense can give 
them a good reason not to. 
</P>
<P>
Deputy Dist. Atty. Marcia Clark said documentation of Robert Bardo's reported 
history of mental illness might persuade them to seek a life sentence. 
</P>
<P>
Bardo, 20, of Tucson, allegedly stalked Schaeffer before shooting her at the 
door of her Fairfax district apartment last July. 
</P>
<P>
Deputy Public Defender Stephen Galindo said his client is receiving medication 
and may plead not guilty by reason of insanity. A psychiatric examination of 
Bardo was ordered by Los Angeles Superior Court Judge Jacqueline Connor. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
BARDO, ROBERT JOHN; SCHAEFFER, REBECCA; MURDERS -- LOS ANGELES; FANS; CAPITAL 
PUNISHMENT 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
