<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: BRADLEY'S LEGAL DEFENSE COSTS EXCEED 
$750,000 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The cost of Los Angeles Mayor Tom Bradley's legal defense in a series of 
conflict-of-interest probes has surpassed $750,000, according to a report 
released Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
The report on fund-raising activity by a committee set up to pay for the 
mayor's defense showed that Bradley owes about $310,000 to lawyers from three 
firms. 
</P>
<P>
In the first six months of 1990, Bradley took in $140,000 toward his defense. 
He has raised a total of $560,000 since the scandal surrounding his 
Administration erupted last year. This year, most expenses have gone to 
attorneys representing Bradley in an ongoing federal probe of the mayor, 
including possible insider trading violations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
