<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE LEGACY OF ART SEIDENBAUM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Art Seidenbaum will be sorely missed by free-lance writers. As former editor of 
Book Review, Art encouraged off-the-beaten-path stories about literary Los 
Angeles that appeared in the phased-out Westview column. 
</P>
<P>
And he could be kind even when he had to be cruel. Rejected articles, when he 
served as Opinion editor, were always accompanied by a comforting word or two 
of explanation. The sight of his name on a Times envelope always set my heart 
aflutter. 
</P>
<P>
And however brief the note's contents, he invariably closed with a kind of life 
motif: "Cheers, Art." 
</P>
<P>
ROSELLE M. LEWIS 
</P>
<P>
Tarzana 
</P>
</TEXT>
