<TEXT>
<P>
Court Rules in Boeing's Favor: The Washington state Supreme Court ruled that 
the families of Japanese nationals who died in the crash of a Boeing 747 five 
years ago in Japan cannot seek damages from the airplane manufacturer in U.S. 
courts. 
</P>
<P>
The ruling, if it stands, means all damage claims must be tried in Japanese 
courts. The ruling was a major victory for Boeing Co. because high damage 
awards are much harder to obtain in Japan. Boeing lost the liability portion of 
the case earlier when a Superior Court judge said faulty repairs resulted in 
cracks in the plane, which led to the crash. 
</P>
