<HEADLINE>
<P>
POLICE ARREST 6 IN CONNECTION WITH DRIVE-BY SHOOTING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LA HABRA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Police on Thursday announced the arrest of four men, including a father and 
son, and two juveniles in connection with a gang-related, drive-by shooting. 
</P>
<P>
The suspects were arrested Monday morning shortly after five rounds were fired 
from a van at a house in the 300 block of Florence Court, La Habra police 
spokeswoman Cindy Knapp said. 
</P>
<P>
"This was a gang-related shooting, a retaliation against another gang," she 
said. 
</P>
<P>
No one was injured in the attack. 
</P>
<P>
Arrested on suspicion of shooting at an inhabited dwelling were Roberto Luna, 
42; his 18-year-old son, Leonard J. Luna; Agapo Acosta, 25; and Jose Guadalupe 
Esquivel, 19. The names of the two juveniles, both 16, were not released 
because of their age. All the suspects are from La Habra. 
</P>
