<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE / REAL ESTATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Michael Flagg Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Resort Designing Booms: Designing resorts is a booming business for some Orange 
County architects. 
</P>
<P>
One of them -- Wimberly, Allison, Tong and Goo -- recently purchased larger 
quarters in Newport Beach's Bay Corporate Center. 
</P>
<P>
The firm paid the Garrick Trust $3.7 million for a 25,000-square-foot building 
on University Drive. The building will be the firm's West Coast headquarters. 
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Peridian, a landscape architect in Irvine, said it will design more 
than 16 acres around a new 18-story Ritz-Carlton hotel in Jakarta, Indonesia. 
</P>
<P>
The 500-room Ritz-Carlton Jakarta is scheduled to open in 1993. Peridian 
designed the grounds of 13 other Ritz-Carltons, including the upscale resort in 
Dana Point. 
</P>
</TEXT>
