<P>
NICHOLS INSTITUTE RAISES $20 MILLION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Nichols Institute, a chain of medical laboratories, said Thursday that it has 
raised $20.2 million from a just-completed sale of common stock and from the 
exercise of stock warrants. 
</P>
<P>
The San Juan Capistrano company sold 2,017,032 common shares, including 250,000 
shares sold by underwriters. The public offering price was $16.625 a share, 
while a per-share price of $15.625 was paid by the offering's two underwriters, 
Kidder, Peabody &amp; Co. and William Blair &amp; Co. 
</P>
