<HEADLINE>
<P>
JAPANESE FUND PH.D. PROGRAM IN PITTSBURGH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PITTSBURGH 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mitsubishi has given $500,000 to the University of Pittsburgh's Joseph Katz 
Graduate School of Business to establish the Mitsubishi Corp. Doctoral 
Fellowship Program in International Management. 
</P>
<P>
Mitsubishi took a majority equity position in Aristech Chemical Corp. of 
Pittsburgh this year as a way of helping Aristech managers buy the company. 
</P>
