<P>
MURPHY WON'T VETO PHILS TRADE; DEAL STILL ON HOLD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ATLANTA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dale Murphy has agreed not to veto a trade that would send him to the Phillies, 
his agent said, but the deal apparently is on hold over the Braves' demand for 
a second player in the package. 
</P>
<P>
Team officials have said the trade centered around sending Murphy to 
Philadelphia for relief pitcher Jeff Parrett. 
</P>
<P>
But the Atlanta Constitution said in today's editions that the Phillies have 
balked at the Braves' demand for another, unidentified player in the package. 
</P>
<P>
